On December 15, in Erode town (Erode, TN), farmers staged a protest against the shandy at Chithode demanding that the management of private shandy not procure adulterated jaggery.

On 5 November, farmers associated with the Kisan Sangharsh Committee staged a protest at Harike (Tarn Taran, Punjab) against the state authorities for not addressing their interests, including alternatives to paddy burning and an increase in allowable moisture content.

On November 5, farmers clashed with the police in Tamando village (Khordha district, Odisha), as they broke the police cordon to enter to Bhubaneswar for a mega convention at Lower PMG, scheduled to put pressure on the government to meet their demands.
Assumed on November 4, in Bailhongal town (Belgaum, Karnataka), farmers staged a protest condemning the arrest warrants issued against Karnataka farmers defaulting repayment of Axis Bank loans.

On 4 November, teachers of Sanjha Adhyapak Morcha, along with supporters from students, parents, and farmers unions, staged a protest at the mini secretariat in Bathinda (Bathinda, Punjab). They demonstrated against recent transfers of protest leaders and demanded regularisation without the large pay cut offered by the education department.

On 4 November, farmers from Muktsar staged a protest and blocked the Muktsar-Kotkapura road near Sarainaga village (Muktsar, Punjab), claiming private millers have been giving them trouble over moisture content in rice paddy and demanding action be taken against the millers.
On November 3, in Koppa Village in Maddur tehsil (Mandya, Karnataka), 50 sugarcane growers staged a protest against the NSL Sugarcane Factory because it had not paid farmers their dues.

On 3 November, farmers associated with BKU Ugrahan and BKU Dakaunda staged a protest and blocked the Sangrur-Bathinda road near Dhanauala (Barnala, Punjab). They were protesting against a delay in purchasing paddy over high moisture content.

On 3 November, farmers aligned with Rashtriya Lok Dal staged a protest and locked down the assistance regional transport office in Muzaffarnagar (Muzaffarnagar, Uttar Pradesh), and blocked the road nearby. They were protesting after the transport department seized 16 tractors, claiming they were too old.

On 1 Nov, former sarpanches and local farmers staged a protest in Thanamandi town (Rajouri, J&K), criticising the Horticulture and Agriculture Department for failing to notify farmers of a nearby awareness camp.

On 1 November, BKU Ugraha and Mazadoor Mukti Morcha members began an protest dharna in front of the Rureke Kalan police station in Barnala (Barnala, Punjab), in protest against the police for failing to take action against people who have blocked access to the fields of a local farmer.

On 1 November, farmers associated with Kisan Sabha Mandi, Lukhuka, staged a protest in the grain market at Fazilka (Fazilka, Punjab) against the 'highhandedness' of private rice traders and claiming that are undercutting the market as a cartel.
On October 31, farmers under the Naba Nirman Krushak Sangathan (NNKS) sat on dharna at Pasupatigada under Tangi block area (Cuttack district, Odisha), demanding price, pension and prestige.
On October 30, in Eluru town (West Godavari, AP), farmers staged a protest demanding that the government release water for withering crops in ayacut lands in remote areas of the Krishna delta.

notes: On October 30, the Krishak Xabha, an organization of the Communist Party of India (CPI), together with local farmers and women's organisations staged a protest in front of the DC's office in Sivasagar city (Sivasagar district, Assam), to demand for the cancelling of the proposed Citizenship (Amendment) Bill, 2016.

On 30 Oct, farmers staged a protest in the Marheen area (Kathua, J&K), demanding the scrapping of the Reliance Insurance Policy for crops. They alleged that the policy has failed to provide compensation to farmers suffering from crop damage, despite money being deducted from farmers' accounts.
On October 29, in Anantapur town (Ananttapur, AP), farmers staged a protest against the Central and State governments for their indifference in addressing the drought issue.

On October 29, in Tetali village in Tanuku tehsil (West Godavari, AP), farmers staged a protest against land acquisition from poor farmers to build autonagar.

On October 29, hundreds of BJP workers along with farmers took out a protest rally and gheraoed the block office in Nuapada city (Nuapada district, Odisha), demanding authorities to declare complete drought in Komna and Khadiyal blocks in the district.

On October 29, in Tandur town in Tandur tehsil (Vikarabad, Telangana), farmers staged a protest and blocked the convoy of caretaker Minister Patnam Mahender Reddy, condemning the Minister for the non-functioning of green gram purchase centre.
On 28 October, a farmer was abducted and beaten, and his wife and daughter harassed, over a sewer dispute between him and a neighbour in Kubbaheri village (Kharar, Sahibzda Ajit Singh Nagar, Punjab).

They also protested against the administration for failing to curb the practice.

On October 26, farmers organisations observed a three-hour Chaka Jam (traffic jam) agitation at several places in Sambalpur city (Sambalpur district, Odisha), to protest the delay in disbursal of crop insurance claims.
